<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-38-0612 </DOCNO><TEXT>The methods of differential thermal, X-ray phase and crystallooptic analysesare used to investigate the interaction in the MF/sub 2/-CoF/sub 2/(M-Mg,Ca, Sr) systems. An incongruently melting compound SrCoF/sub 4/ existingin the 750-784 deg C temperature range appear in the SrF/sub 2/-CoF/sub2/ system. The structure is rhombic with lattice parameters a=14.45,b=3.92, c5.66 +-0.011 A. Eutectics coordinates are 56 mol.% of CoF/sub2/.776 deg C. Eutectics reflection indices are Ng=1.483; Nm=1.472. Solidsolutions up to 1 mol.% appear on the basis of both components besidethe component in the SrF/sub 2/-CoF/sub 2/ system.</TEXT></DOC>